  "text": "Our observations of bone tunnel widening and embedding of the screw in a trough-shaped recess of the tibial tunnel in the IF group indicates a mechanically contributed tunnel enlargement by drilling the interference screw into the soft bone of the tibial metaphysis. These results confirm the findings by other investigations, who demonstrated that an interference screw not only compresses the graft in the tunnel but also leads to a bone tunnel dilatation by itself [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
